<DocsLayout title="Ansible Deployment">
  <h1>Ansible Deployment</h1>
  <p>
    The EncodeSwarmr Ansible collection automates installation and configuration of controllers and agents across
    on-premises Linux hosts (and Windows agents via WinRM). Playbooks are idempotent and safe to re-run.
  </p>

  <h2>Deployment Modes</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Mode</th><th>Description</th><th>Use Case</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Standard (bare-metal)</td>
        <td>Installs .deb/.rpm packages and configures systemd services</td>
        <td>Production on-prem with existing OS</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Docker Compose</td>
        <td>Deploys controller via Docker Compose on the target host</td>
        <td>Quick setup; easier updates</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>HA with Patroni</td>
        <td>Two controllers + Patroni-managed PostgreSQL + HAProxy</td>
        <td>Production with fault tolerance</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>

  <h3>Control Node (where you run Ansible)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Ansible 2.15 or later</li>
    <li>Python packages: <code>psycopg2-binary</code>, <code>pywinrm</code> (for Windows agents), <code>boto3</code> (optional, for dynamic inventory)</li>
    <li>Ansible collections: <code>community.general</code>, <code>community.postgresql</code>, <code>ansible.windows</code></li>
    <li>SSH access to all Linux target hosts (key-based recommended)</li>
    <li>WinRM configured on all Windows agent hosts (see Windows section)</li>
  </ul>

  <pre><code># Install Ansible and Python dependencies
pip install ansible psycopg2-binary pywinrm

# Install required Ansible collections
ansible-galaxy collection install community.general community.postgresql ansible.windows</code></pre>

  <h3>Other Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>All target hosts must be able to reach the controller on ports <strong>8080</strong> and <strong>9443</strong></li>
    <li>Shared NFS/SMB storage mounted at the same path on controller and all Linux agents</li>
    <li>PostgreSQL 15+ accessible from the controller host (can be managed by Ansible or external)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Quick Start — Standard Deployment</h2>
  <pre><code># 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/badskater/encodeswarmr.git
cd encodeswarmr/deploy/ansible

# 2. Copy and edit the inventory
cp inventory/hosts.yml.example inventory/hosts.yml
$EDITOR inventory/hosts.yml

# 3. Copy and edit variables
cp group_vars/all.yml.example group_vars/all.yml
$EDITOR group_vars/all.yml

# 4. Run the full deployment
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/site.yml</code></pre>

  <h2>Available Playbooks</h2>

  <h3><code>playbooks/site.yml</code></h3>
  <p>Full deployment: configures all hosts in one run. Equivalent to running <code>controller.yml</code> then <code>agents.yml</code>.</p>
  <pre><code>ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/site.yml</code></pre>

  <h3><code>playbooks/controller.yml</code></h3>
  <p>Deploy or update the controller only. Skips agent hosts entirely.</p>
  <pre><code>ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/controller.yml</code></pre>

  <h3><code>playbooks/agents.yml</code></h3>
  <p>Deploy or update agents only. Use <code>--limit</code> to target specific hosts or groups:</p>
  <pre><code># All agents
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/agents.yml

# Specific Linux agent group
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/agents.yml --limit linux_agents

# Specific Windows agent group
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/agents.yml --limit windows_agents

# Single host
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/agents.yml --limit encode-win-01</code></pre>

  <h3><code>playbooks/ha.yml</code></h3>
  <p>Configure high-availability controller pair. Two sub-modes are supported:</p>

  <h4>Standalone HA (HAProxy + two controllers)</h4>
  <pre><code>ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/ha.yml</code></pre>

  <h4>HA with Patroni (HAProxy + two controllers + Patroni PostgreSQL)</h4>
  <pre><code>ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/ha.yml \
  -e "patroni_enabled=true"</code></pre>

  <h3><code>playbooks/upgrade.yml</code></h3>
  <p>Rolling upgrade with health-check gates. The playbook upgrades one host at a time and waits for the service to report healthy before continuing.</p>
  <pre><code># Upgrade to latest release
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/upgrade.yml

# Pin to a specific version
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/upgrade.yml \
  -e "encodeswarmr_version=1.2.0"

# Upgrade only controllers
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/upgrade.yml \
  --tags controller

# Upgrade only agents
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/upgrade.yml \
  --tags agent</code></pre>

  <h3><code>playbooks/docker-compose/deploy.yml</code></h3>
  <p>Alternative playbook that deploys the controller as a Docker Compose stack instead of a native package.</p>
  <pre><code>ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml \
  playbooks/docker-compose/deploy.yml</code></pre>

  <h2>Variable Reference</h2>

  <h3><code>group_vars/all.yml</code></h3>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Variable</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>encodeswarmr_version</code></td><td><code>latest</code></td><td>Release tag to install (e.g. <code>1.2.0</code>)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>encodeswarmr_user</code></td><td><code>encodeswarmr</code></td><td>System user that runs the service</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>encodeswarmr_config_dir</code></td><td><code>/etc/encodeswarmr</code></td><td>Directory for config files and certs</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>encodeswarmr_data_dir</code></td><td><code>/var/lib/encodeswarmr</code></td><td>Persistent data directory</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>db_host</code></td><td><code>localhost</code></td><td>PostgreSQL host</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>db_port</code></td><td><code>5432</code></td><td>PostgreSQL port</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>db_name</code></td><td><code>encodeswarmr</code></td><td>Database name</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>db_user</code></td><td><code>encodeswarmr</code></td><td>Database user</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>db_password</code></td><td><em>required</em></td><td>Database password (use Ansible Vault)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>secret_key</code></td><td><em>required</em></td><td>32-byte random secret for session signing</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>mtls_enabled</code></td><td><code>true</code></td><td>Generate and distribute mTLS certificates</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>log_level</code></td><td><code>info</code></td><td>Log verbosity: <code>debug</code>, <code>info</code>, <code>warn</code>, <code>error</code></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

