  <h2>Windows Agent Setup via WinRM</h2>
  <p>Run these commands on each Windows agent host to enable WinRM for Ansible:</p>
  <pre><code># PowerShell — run as Administrator on each Windows agent

# Enable WinRM with HTTPS
winrm quickconfig -q
winrm set winrm/config/service '@&#123;AllowUnencrypted="false"&#125;'
winrm set winrm/config/service/auth '@&#123;Basic="true"&#125;'

# Create a self-signed certificate for WinRM HTTPS
$cert = New-SelfSignedCertificate `
  -DnsName $env:COMPUTERNAME `
  -CertStoreLocation "cert:\LocalMachine\My"

# Create HTTPS listener
New-Item -Path WSMan:\Localhost\Listener `
  -Transport HTTPS `
  -Address * `
  -CertificateThumbPrint $cert.Thumbprint `
  -Force

# Open firewall
netsh advfirewall firewall add rule name="WinRM HTTPS" `
  dir=in action=allow protocol=TCP localport=5986

# Restart WinRM
Restart-Service WinRM</code></pre>

  <p>Add Windows hosts to your Ansible inventory with WinRM connection settings:</p>
  <pre><code># inventory/hosts.yml
all:
  children:
    controllers:
      hosts:
        controller-01:
          ansible_host: 192.168.1.10
    agents:
      children:
        linux_agents:
          hosts:
            encode-linux-01:
              ansible_host: 192.168.1.20
        windows_agents:
          hosts:
            encode-win-01:
              ansible_host: 192.168.1.30
              ansible_user: Administrator
              ansible_password: "&#123;&#123; vault_win_password &#125;&#125;"
              ansible_connection: winrm
              ansible_winrm_transport: ntlm
              ansible_winrm_port: 5986
              ansible_winrm_scheme: https
              ansible_winrm_server_cert_validation: ignore</code></pre>

  <h2>mTLS Certificates</h2>
  <p>
    When <code>mtls_enabled: true</code> (the default), Ansible automatically generates a CA and all certificates on
    the Ansible control node and distributes them to the appropriate hosts. Certificates are regenerated only if
    missing or expired.
  </p>
  <p>To use your own pre-generated certificates instead, set <code>mtls_enabled: false</code> and provide the
    certificate paths via <code>tls_ca_cert</code>, <code>tls_server_cert</code>, <code>tls_server_key</code>,
    <code>tls_agent_cert</code>, and <code>tls_agent_key</code> variables.</p>

  <h2>Docker Compose Alternative</h2>
  <p>
    The <code>docker-compose/deploy.yml</code> playbook configures Docker on the controller host and deploys
    EncodeSwarmr as a Compose stack. This is useful when you prefer container-based management.
  </p>
  <pre><code># group_vars/controllers.yml additions for Docker mode
deploy_mode: docker-compose
docker_compose_dir: /opt/encodeswarmr
docker_image_tag: "&#123;&#123; encodeswarmr_version &#125;&#125;"</code></pre>

  <h2>Upgrading</h2>
  <pre><code># Rolling upgrade — health-check gated, one host at a time
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/upgrade.yml

# Skip confirmation prompts
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/upgrade.yml -e "auto_confirm=true"

# Dry-run (check mode)
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/upgrade.yml --check</code></pre>

  <h2>Tags Reference</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Tag</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>controller</code></td><td>All controller tasks</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>agent</code></td><td>All agent tasks</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>packages</code></td><td>Install/upgrade packages only</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>config</code></td><td>Write configuration files only (no package changes)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>certs</code></td><td>Generate and distribute mTLS certificates</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>postgres</code></td><td>PostgreSQL installation and database setup</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>haproxy</code></td><td>HAProxy installation and configuration</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>systemd</code></td><td>Manage systemd unit files and service state</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>tools</code></td><td>Install encode tools (FFmpeg, SVT-AV1, etc.)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>never</code></td><td>Tasks skipped by default; use <code>--tags never</code> to run (e.g. reset DB)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <pre><code># Example: only update config files without touching packages
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/site.yml --tags config

# Example: only regenerate certificates
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/site.yml --tags certs</code></pre>

  <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>

  <h3>Certificate Errors</h3>
  <p>If agents fail to connect with TLS errors:</p>
  <pre><code># Force certificate regeneration
ansible-playbook -i inventory/hosts.yml playbooks/site.yml \
  --tags certs -e "force_cert_regen=true"</code></pre>

  <h3>Controller Not Starting</h3>
  <pre><code># Check service status and logs
ansible controllers -i inventory/hosts.yml \
  -m shell -a "systemctl status encodeswarmr-controller"

ansible controllers -i inventory/hosts.yml \
  -m shell -a "journalctl -u encodeswarmr-controller -n 50"</code></pre>

  <h3>Agent Not Starting</h3>
  <pre><code># Linux agent
ansible linux_agents -i inventory/hosts.yml \
  -m shell -a "journalctl -u encodeswarmr-agent -n 50"

# Windows agent (via WinRM)
ansible windows_agents -i inventory/hosts.yml \
  -m win_shell -a "Get-EventLog -LogName Application -Source EncodeSwarmr -Newest 20 | Format-List"</code></pre>

  <h3>WinRM Connection Issues</h3>
  <pre><code># Test WinRM connectivity from the control node
ansible encode-win-01 -i inventory/hosts.yml -m win_ping

# If it fails, verify WinRM is running on the Windows host:
# (run on Windows host)
Get-Service WinRM
Test-WSMan -ComputerName localhost -UseSSL</code></pre>

  <h3>PostgreSQL Connection Refused</h3>
  <pre><code># Check PostgreSQL is listening
ansible controllers -i inventory/hosts.yml \
  -m shell -a "pg_isready -h localhost -p 5432"

# Check pg_hba.conf allows the encodeswarmr user
ansible controllers -i inventory/hosts.yml \
  -m shell -a "grep encodeswarmr /etc/postgresql/*/main/pg_hba.conf"</code></pre>

  <h3>NFS Mount Issues on Agents</h3>
  <pre><code># Verify NFS mount is active on all agent hosts
ansible agents -i inventory/hosts.yml \
  -m shell -a "mountpoint -q /mnt/media &amp;&amp; echo OK || echo NOT MOUNTED"

# Re-mount if needed
ansible agents -i inventory/hosts.yml \
  -m shell -a "mount /mnt/media" --become</code></pre>
